verbose_text: In contrast, crossing Fh1betaKO mice with mice stably expressing either full-length human FH (Fh1betaKO+ FH) or cytoplasmic FH (FH cyt) (Fh1betaKO+ FH cyt) fully reversed the glucose intolerance tested in stage III mice and restored the mRNA expression of Egln3 and Hmox1 (XREF_FIG Q and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY B-S1D), and these mice were normoglycemic for> 1 year.
